what are *args and **kwargs?

1.*args
Accepts multiple positional arguments.
def add(*args):
    print(sum(args))
add(10, 20, 30))

o/p-->60


2.**kwargs
Accepts multiple keyword arguments.
def info(**kwargs):
    print(kwargs)
info(name="Ayushi", age=22)

o/p-->{'name': 'Ayushi', 'age': 22}
is a dictionary.


3.both
def demo(*args, **kwargs):
    print(args)
    print(kwargs)
demo(1, 2, 3, name="Ayushi", city="Pune")

o/p-->(1, 2, 3)
{'name': 'Ayushi', 'city': 'Pune'}
